body_html:
thanks @mrry! Are you referring to #10151 with your answer? It seems to me as it's not about what the parsing function returns but rather what we pack into tf.parse_single_example() e.g.

dataset = tf.contrib.data.TFRecordDataset(filenames)
parse_fn = lambda r: [tf.parse_single_example(r, {"f1": tf.VarLenFeature(tf.int64)})]
dataset.map(parse_fn)

This wouldn't work as well.

body:
thanks @mrry! Are you referring to #10151 with your answer? It seems to me as it's not about what the parsing function returns but rather what we pack into `tf.parse_single_example()` e.g.
```python
dataset = tf.contrib.data.TFRecordDataset(filenames)
parse_fn = lambda r: [tf.parse_single_example(r, {"f1": tf.VarLenFeature(tf.int64)})]
dataset.map(parse_fn)
```
This wouldn't work as well.
